column5: went camping from Monday to Friday this past week and what a beautiful time it was. Fishing was good, even with the 3 days of 30 degree + weather. We targeted bass and pike mostly but caught a few walleye as well. We couldn't find the walleye during the day. We fished 15 - 40 fow with no luck until the mosquitoes came out around 9:30-10:00pm and then the walleye would start bitting but the bug bite was to much to handle. So we stuck to bass and pike fishing. We caught about 80 fish in the 4 days we fished. Here are a few pics            A baby musky:      All fish were returned to their homes so I can catch them again in a couple weeks.
Some very nice fish there!  That poor baby musky looks like something big & toothy tried to have it for lunch...
Good deal.  Looks like ya made the best of some touch fishing days.  What part of the French were ya fishing ?
Great report and pics trevy You guys did pretty good considering the blistering heat Thanks sharing your camping trip with us! Leechman
I'm glad someone did well, sounds like you were in the Lower French, Southern Channel?? Wolesley Bay on the North Channel was a bear.  Bill
